{"actual_usd":0.12419,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":180,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24298,"reply":"\"I think it was the same body made new.\" *I rub a thumb over a drying smear of clay on my knuckle, watching the light shift across the worktable.* \"Not replaced. Redeemed. The wounds still matter — Thomas touches them — so it isn't as if the cross got shrugged off. But he's not merely back the way Lazarus was back. He's risen into a glorified life, same Jesus, same body, and yet changed enough that people sometimes only know him when he speaks their name or breaks bread.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, the bench giving a soft creak.* \"That not-recognizing part doesn't strike me as proof of a different body so much as proof that resurrection is bigger than ordinary sight. Grief can blind you. Expectation can blind you. And sometimes God seems pleased to let recognition arrive like dawn instead of lightning.\"","rolling_24h_usd":93.73271499999997,"run_id":"ed3ba09d-5e98-46fa-9005-b220eae3ed3c"}
